  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       SCROLL STORYTELLING — OBSERVERSHIP NARRATIVE
       ════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="story-section" id="observership">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="story-layout">

        <!-- Sticky sidebar -->
        <div class="story-sidebar">
          <div class="story-sidebar__visual card">
            <p class="label" style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-sm);">Observership Overview</p>
            <div class="story-meta">
              <div class="story-meta__item">
                <span class="story-meta__label">Hospital</span>
                <span class="story-meta__val">CKS Hospital, Jaipur</span>
              </div>
              <div class="story-meta__item">
                <span class="story-meta__label">Supervisor</span>
                <span class="story-meta__val">Dr. Prakash Chandwani</span>
              </div>
              <div class="story-meta__item">
                <span class="story-meta__label">Speciality</span>
                <span class="story-meta__val">Cardiology &amp; Surgery</span>
              </div>
              <div class="story-meta__item">
                <span class="story-meta__label">Duration</span>
                <span class="story-meta__val">March 2026</span>
              </div>
              <div class="story-meta__item">
                <span class="story-meta__label">Type</span>
                <span class="story-meta__val">Clinical Observership</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div style="background: var(--c-accent); border: 1px solid var(--c-border); border-radius: var(--r-lg); padding: var(--sp-md);">
            <p class="label" style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-xs);">Competency Linked</p>
            <p style="font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--c-text);">Medical Expert</p>
            <p style="font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--c-muted); margin-top: 0.25rem; line-height: 1.5;">Clinical reasoning · Patient care · Procedural knowledge · Reflective practice</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Scroll story items -->
        <div class="story-items">

          <!-- Intro -->
          <div class="story-item" id="story-intro">
            <div class="story-item__tag">
              <svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/></svg>
              Overview
            </div>
            <h2 class="story-item__title">Observership at CKS Hospital</h2>
            <p class="story-item__text">
              During March 2026, I undertook a clinical observership under Dr. Prakash Chandwani, a renowned cardiologist at CKS Hospital, Jaipur. This experience provided direct exposure to patient management, multidisciplinary care, and operative procedures across various departments.
            </p>
            <p class="story-item__text" style="margin-top: var(--sp-sm);">
              This observership improved my ability to connect classroom knowledge with real clinical practice. It also enhanced my observational skills, understanding of patient-centered care, and appreciation for teamwork within healthcare systems.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Ward Rounds -->
          <div class="story-item" id="story-ward">
            <div class="story-item__tag">
              <svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><path d="M3 9l9-7 9 7v11a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2z"/></svg>
              Ward Rounds
            </div>
            <h2 class="story-item__title">Daily Ward Rounds &amp; Patient Review</h2>
            <p class="story-item__text">
              My daily responsibilities involved accompanying the clinical team during ward rounds, where I observed patient evaluations, clinical discussions, and decision-making processes. I engaged in reviewing patient histories, monitoring progress, and understanding treatment plans.
            </p>
            <p class="story-item__text" style="margin-top: var(--sp-sm);">
              This allowed me to appreciate the importance of structured clinical reasoning and continuity of care. Observing how the senior physicians moved fluidly between clinical assessment, patient communication, and treatment adjustment deepened my respect for the cognitive complexity of medicine.
            </p>
            <div style="margin-top: var(--sp-md); padding: var(--sp-md); background: var(--c-accent); border-radius: var(--r-lg); border-left: 3px solid var(--c-secondary);">
              <p class="italic-accent" style="font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.6;">"Continuity of care is not a schedule — it is a relationship between a clinician's understanding and a patient's evolving condition."</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- ICU -->
          <div class="story-item" id="story-icu">
            <div class="story-item__tag">
              <svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><path d="M22 12h-4l-3 9L9 3l-3 9H2"/></svg>
              ICU Exposure
            </div>
            <h2 class="story-item__title">Intensive Care Unit &amp; Critical Monitoring</h2>
            <p class="story-item__text">
              I also spent time in the intensive care unit, where I was introduced to critical care monitoring, including interpretation of arterial blood gases and patient stability parameters. This exposure enhanced my understanding of acute patient management and the importance of timely intervention.
            </p>
            <p class="story-item__text" style="margin-top: var(--sp-sm);">
              The ICU environment was transformative — the pace, precision, and collaborative urgency of critical care challenged me to think more systematically about physiological parameters and the sequencing of clinical interventions. I observed how small deviations in ABG values translated into immediate changes in management plans.
            </p>
            <div style="margin-top: var(--sp-md); display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.5rem;">
              <span class="tag">ABG Interpretation</span>
              <span class="tag">Critical Care Monitoring</span>
              <span class="tag">Acute Management</span>
              <span class="tag">Haemodynamic Assessment</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Surgery -->
          <div class="story-item" id="story-surgery">
            <div class="story-item__tag">
              <svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3"/><path d="M12 1v6m0 6v6M1 12h6m6 0h6"/></svg>
              Surgical Exposure
            </div>
            <h2 class="story-item__title">Surgical Procedures Observed</h2>
            <p class="story-item__text">
              Additionally, I observed multiple surgical procedures including tympanic membrane grafting, knee replacement surgery, prostate enlargement surgery, and vocal cord biopsy. During these procedures, the surgeons provided step-by-step explanations of the operative techniques, anatomical structures, and clinical rationale behind each intervention.
            </p>
            <p class="story-item__text" style="margin-top: var(--sp-sm);">
              A particularly impactful experience was observing prostate surgery while simultaneously studying the same topic academically. <strong style="color: var(--c-text);">This integration of theoretical learning with real surgical exposure significantly strengthened my understanding and retention of the subject</strong> — the most important insight of the entire observership.
            </p>
            <div style="margin-top: var(--sp-md); display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 0.5rem;">
              <div style="background: var(--c-accent); border: 1px solid var(--c-border); border-radius: var(--r-md); padding: 0.75rem; text-align: center;">
                <p style="font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--c-secondary);">4</p>
                <p style="font-size: 0.78rem; color: var(--c-muted);">Surgical Procedures</p>
              </div>
              <div style="background: var(--c-accent); border: 1px solid var(--c-border); border-radius: var(--r-md); padding: 0.75rem; text-align: center;">
                <p style="font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--c-secondary);">3+</p>
                <p style="font-size: 0.78rem; color: var(--c-muted);">Specialties Covered</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Reflection -->
          <div class="story-item" id="story-reflection">
            <div class="story-item__tag">
              <svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><path d="M1 12s4-8 11-8 11 8 11 8-4 8-11 8-11-8-11-8z"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3"/></svg>
              Reflection
            </div>
            <h2 class="story-item__title">Learning &amp; Moving Forward</h2>
            <p class="story-item__text">
              This observership improved my ability to connect classroom knowledge with real clinical practice. It enhanced my observational skills, understanding of patient-centered care, and appreciation for teamwork within healthcare systems.
            </p>
            <p class="story-item__text" style="margin-top: var(--sp-sm);">
              Moving forward, I aim to build on this experience by developing stronger clinical reasoning skills and actively engaging in patient interaction opportunities to further enhance my competencies as a future physician.
            </p>
            <div style="margin-top: var(--sp-lg);" class="btn-group">
              <a href="competencies.html" class="btn btn-primary">
                View All Competencies
                <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
              </a>
              <a href="journey.html" class="btn btn-secondary">Academic Journey</a>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div><!-- /story-items -->
      </div><!-- /story-layout -->
    </div>
  </section>

