  <section class="section" style="background: var(--c-accent);">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid-2">
        <div class="fade-left">
          <span class="section-header__eyebrow">Learning Approach</span>
          <h2 class="heading-lg" style="margin: var(--sp-sm) 0 var(--sp-md);">Reflection &amp; Learning Approach</h2>
          <div class="divider"></div>
          <p class="body-lg" style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-md);">
            I adopt a structured reflective approach to learning, analysing each experience through observation, evaluation, and application. This allows me to identify strengths, recognise gaps, and continuously improve my clinical understanding and professional development.
          </p>
          <p class="body-md" style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-lg);">
            Reflection is not retrospective — it is an active, ongoing practice that shapes how I engage with every clinical encounter, academic session, and professional interaction.
          </p>
          <div class="btn-group">
            <a href="competencies.html" class="btn btn-primary">All Competencies</a>
            <a href="index.html" class="btn btn-secondary">Back to Home</a>
